{{notability|date=December 2016}} {{Infobox journal | title = Fashion Theory | cover = | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Fash. Theory | discipline = [[Fashion]] | editor = Valerie Steele | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | history = 1997-present | frequency = 5/year | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSN = 1362-704X | eISSN = 1751-7419 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = 57378034 | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=rfft20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rfft20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rfft20 | link2-name = Online archive }} '''''Fashion Theory: The Journal of Dress, Body & Culture''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Routledge]]. It was established in 1997 and covers the study of [[fashion]], including aspects from [[sociology]], [[art history]], consumption studies, and [[anthropology]]. In the first editorial, the founding [[editor-in-chief]] [[Valerie Steele]] ([[Fashion Institute of Technology|The Museum at the Fashion Institute of Technology]]) stated that the journal approaches fashion "as the cultural construction of the embodied identity".<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.2752/136270497779754589 |title=Letter from the Editor |year=1997 |last1=Steele |first1=Valerie |journal=Fashion Theory |volume=1 |pages=1}}</ref> The journal investigates issues of body in society but also includes studies on practices of production, dissemination, and consumption of dress. In addition, it includes reviews of exhibitions and academic publications.
