{{Infobox musical composition | Name = ''Symphony No. 10'' | Composer = [[Philip Glass]] | Form = [[Symphony]] | Duration = 30 minutes<ref name="Glass10">[http://www.philipglass.com/music/compositions/Symphony10.php Symphony No. 10] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150303234359/http://www.philipglass.com/music/compositions/Symphony10.php |date=2015-03-03 }}</ref> | Period = [[Contemporary classical music|Contemporary]] | Style = [[Postmodern music|Postmodern]], [[Minimalist music|minimalist]] | Composed = 2011-2012 | Publisher = | Premiere_date = {{Start date|2012|8|9}} | Premiere_location = Grand Théâtre de Provence in [[Aix-en-Provence]], [[France]] | Premiere_conductor = [[Dennis Russell Davies]] | Premiere_performers = Orchestre Français des Jeunes }}
'''Symphony No. 10''' is the tenth symphony by the American composer [[Philip Glass]]. The work was commissioned by the Orchestre Français des Jeunes and premiered August 9, 2012, with [[Dennis Russell Davies]] conducting the Orchestre Français des Jeunes at the Grand Théâtre de Provence in [[Aix-en-Provence]], [[France]].<ref name="Glass10" /> The piece had its [[United Kingdom]] premiere July 31, 2013 at [[The Proms]] in [[Royal Albert Hall]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Prom 25: Zappa – The Adventures of Greggery Peccary |work=[[BBC]] |date=2013 |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/proms/archive/search/2010s/2013/july-31/14638 |accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref>
==Composition== The symphony reworks music originally written as ''Los paisajes del rio'' for the [[Philip Glass Ensemble]], premiered at the 2008 Expo Zaragoza.<ref>{{cite web |last=Johnson |first=Daniel Stephen |title=Philip Glass Blasts Past Beethoven with Fireworks of 10th Symphony |publisher=[[WQXR-FM]] |date=July 27, 2015 |url=http://www.wqxr.org/#!/story/philip-glass-blasts-past-beethoven-fireworks-10th-symphony/ |accessdate=November 3, 2015}}</ref> Due to the famed [[curse of the ninth]], Glass composed the piece before the premiere of his [[Symphony No. 9 (Glass)|Ninth Symphony]].<ref name="FT">{{cite web |last=Saer |first=Arabella |title=Glass's 10th Symphony, Grand Théâtre de Provence, Aix-en-Provence |work=[[Financial Times]] |date=August 12, 2012 |url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/2/c4127220-e2da-11e1-bf02-00144feab49a.html |accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref>
===Instrumentation=== The work is scored for [[piccolo]], two [[Western concert flute|flutes]], two [[oboe]]s, three [[clarinet]]s (II doubled on [[E-flat clarinet]], III doubled on [[bass clarinet]]), two [[bassoon]]s, four [[French horn]]s, three [[trumpet]]s, two [[trombone]]s, [[Types of trombone#bass trombone|bass trombone]], [[tuba]], [[timpani]], six [[Percussion instrument|percussionists]] ([[Tubular bells|chimes]], [[glockenspiel]], [[xylophone]], [[marimba]]s, [[Triangle (musical instrument)|triangle]], [[anvil]], [[gong|tamtam]], [[clash cymbals]], [[castanets]], [[wood block]], [[snare drum]], [[tenor drum]], [[bass drum]]), [[celesta]], [[piano]], [[Pedal harp|harp]], and [[String section|strings]] ([[violin]]s I & II, [[viola]]s, [[violoncello]]s, and [[double bass]]es).<ref name="Glass10" />
==Reception== Reviewing the world premiere at the Grand Théâtre de Provence, Arabella Saer of the ''[[Financial Times]]'' lauded the symphony, writing:{{quote|There were enough typical Glass elements – repeated arpeggios, chugging chords, cross-rhythms and pared-down harmony – for the 35-minute piece to win no new converts. But there was also a cool, fresh energy about it, arising as much, perhaps, from the ''jeunesse'' of the players and the sleek, modern hall (only five years old), as from the fact that Glass must have had a youth orchestra – ''this'' youth orchestra – in mind when he wrote it.<ref name="FT" />}} Andrew Clements of ''[[The Guardian]]'' later opined, "Its extrovert origins as latter-day fireworks music remain clear, though, as Glass's orchestration, with its brassy edge and martial percussion – lots of snare drum – underlines in Davies's performance."<ref>{{cite web |last=Clements |first=Andrew |title=Glass: Symphony No 10; Concert Overture CD review – an extrovert celebration |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=20 August 2015 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/aug/20/glass-symphony-no-10-concert-overture-cd-review |accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref> Pwyll ap Siôn of ''[[Gramophone (magazine)|Gramophone]]'' also gave the work moderate praise, writing:{{quote|The work opens and ends effectively enough with a darkly exuberant first and flamboyant fifth. Deprived of their extra-musical clothing, some of the other movements lack variety and substance, however. The slow second's gradually unfolding two-note melody is only enlivened by pulsing patterns in percussion and brass, while the third’s endless tonic-dominant oscillations and the fourth’s paradiddle patterns struggle to hold interest.<ref>{{cite web |last=Siôn |first=Pwyll ap |title=GLASS Symphony No 10. Concert Overture |work=[[Gramophone (magazine)|Gramophone]] |date=September 2015 |url=http://www.gramophone.co.uk/review/glass-symphony-no-10-concert-overture |accessdate=November 4, 2015}}</ref>}}
