{{Infobox artist | name = Victor Ivanovich Korovin | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = December 31, 1936 | birth_place = [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] | death_date = July 6, 1991 | death_place = [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] | field = [[Painting]] | citizenship = [[USSR]], [[Russian Federation]] | nationality = | training = [[Tavricheskaya Art School]] | movement = [[Realism (visual art)|Realism]] | works = | patrons = | awards = }}
'''Victor Ivanovich Korovin''' ({{lang-ru|Виктор Иванович Коровин}}; December 31, 1936, [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] — July 6, 1991, [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]]) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Russians|Russian]] painter, a member of the [[Saint Petersburg Union of Artists|Leningrad Union of Artists]],<ref>''Справочник членов Ленинградской организации Союза художников РСФСР.'' Л., Художник РСФСР, 1987. C.62.</ref> who lived and worked in [[Leningrad]]. Victor Korovin regarded as one of representatives of the [[Leningrad School of Painting|Leningrad school of painting]],<ref>''Sergei V. Ivanov. Unknown Socialist Realism. The Leningrad School.'' Saint Petersburg, NP-Print Edition, 2007. P.398.</ref> most famous for his landscape paintings. Died in an accident.
